# Analytics Configuration
# Replace these placeholder values with your actual tracking IDs

# Google Analytics 4 Measurement ID
# Get this from: https://analytics.google.com/
# Format: G-XXXXXXXXXX
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Microsoft Clarity Project ID  
# Get this from: https://clarity.microsoft.com/
# Format: random string like "abcd1234"
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID=CLARITY_PROJECT_ID

# Google Search Console Verification
# Get this from: https://search.google.com/search-console
# Format: random string for meta tag verification
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_VERIFICATION=verification-code-placeholder

# Hotjar Site ID (Optional)
# Get this from: https://www.hotjar.com/
# Format: numeric ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_HOTJAR_ID=

# Facebook Pixel ID (Optional)
# Get this from: https://business.facebook.com/
# Format: numeric ID  
NEXT_PUBLIC_FACEBOOK_PIXEL_ID=

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace placeholder values with your actual tracking IDs
# 3. Restart your development server
# 4. The analytics will automatically start tracking

# Production Notes:
# - Add these environment variables to your hosting platform (Vercel, Netlify, etc.)
# - Make sure NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix is included for client-side access
# - Keep your tracking IDs secure and don't commit real values to git
